  "text": "Our finding that, in the absence of FXN but in the presence of reFDX2, the rate of cluster assembly on ISCU(M108I) is significantly higher than on ISCU is in line with earlier studies in yeast. [CITATION_1] This higher rate of cluster assembly may explain, in part, why the ISCU(M108I) variant in yeast cells has been found to escape the requirement for FXN.",
